# ParikshaSetu — Testing Guide: Phases 6, 7, 8, 9 & 10
### (Simultaneous Frontend + Backend)

This guide walks you through every new module in one continuous session, verifying the **browser UI and backend terminal logs together** at each step.

---

## 1. Prerequisites & Setup

### Servers Running
Open **three terminals** in `C:\Users\Devraj\Desktop\ParikshaSetu\`:

**Terminal 1 — FastAPI backend:**
```powershell
venv\Scripts\uvicorn apps.api.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

**Terminal 2 — Celery worker (Windows solo pool):**
```powershell
venv\Scripts\celery -A apps.api.workers.celery_app.celery_app worker --loglevel=info -P solo
```
> If Redis is not running, tasks execute synchronously (Eager Mode). The `[Celery] Redis is not reachable. Falling back to Eager Mode` line will appear — this is fine for local testing.

**Terminal 3 — Next.js frontend:**
```powershell
cd apps\web && npm run dev
```

### Supabase Storage Buckets (One-Time)
In your Supabase Dashboard → **Storage** → **New bucket**:
- `question-papers-vault` → Private (no public access)
- `answer-sheet-uploads` → Private (no public access)

### Starting State
You need an exam that has already gone through Phases 3–5:
- Status: `ADMIT_CARDS_ISSUED`
- Mode: `OFFLINE` (for printing & transit tabs)
- At least **1 center** with at least **2 rooms**
- At least **1 student** with an allocated center + issued admit card

Login as **Agency Head** at:
```
http://national-testing-agency.localhost:3000/agency/login
```
Navigate to the exam workspace:
```
http://national-testing-agency.localhost:3000/agency/exams/[examId]
```

